# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SIFTA / Alice  —  ANTON_SIFTA repository .gitignore
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Steve-Jobs-grade clean: only the living organism body is tracked.
# Runtime state, vision frames, simulation residue, personal notes, and
# build artifacts are NOT tracked.  The body's macOS-style skeleton
# stays:
#
#     Applications/  System/  Documents/  Kernel/  Library/  Network/
#     Organs/  Security/  Simulations/  Utilities/  Vendor/
#     assets/  bin/  data/  distro/  exports/  launchd/  schemas/
#     scripts/  skills/  static/  tests/  tools/
#
# Plus the root files defined by the SIFTA distro spec:
#
#     README.md  README.ro.md  LICENSE
#     .gitignore  .gitattributes
#     pytest.ini  requirements.txt  config.json
#     integrity_manifest.json  node_registry.json
#     sifta_os_desktop.py  siftactl.py  sifta_mcp_server.py
#     sifta-skills.sh  SIFTA OS.command  !RunPhysarumContradictionLab.command
#
# Everything else asks itself: am I (a) reproducible from the canonical
# code, (b) personal to this hardware, or (c) regenerable at boot? If
# any of those are yes, it should NOT be tracked here.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ── Large downloaded robot kinematics (fixture slice lives in tests/fixtures/) ─
assets/robotics/irb2400/datasetIRB2400.csv
assets/robotics/arkoma/*.csv

# ── macOS debris ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
